<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<title> Forms in HTML</title>
	</head>

	<body>
			<form method = "post" action = "forms.html"> 
			
					<label> User name : </label>
					<input type = "text" name = "userName" /> <br>
					
					<label> Password : </label>
					<input type = "password" name = "password" /> <br>
					
					<input type = "radio" name = "gender" value ="male" /><label> Male </label><br>
					
				    <input type = "radio" name = "gender" value ="female" /><label> Female </label> 					
					<br>
					
					<label> Class </label>
					<select name = "class"> 
						<option value = "IT"> B.Tech CS </option>
						<option value = "CS"> B.Tech IT </option>
					</select>
					<br>
					
					<input type = "reset" name = "reset" value= "RESET!" />
					
					<input type = "submit" name = "login" value = "login" /><br>
					
					<input type = "checkbox" name = "rm" value = "1" /> <label> Remember me </label>
			</form>
	</body>
</html>


<!--FORM : an object to collect information
			it first accepts data from user then sends it to the server (another/same web page)
			
	form element of html
	
	controls - text field    <input>   input is a self closing tag
			   radio         <input>
			   checkbox      <input>
			   drop-down     <select>
			   text area     <textarea>
			   button        <button>
			   submit button <input>   
			   reset button  <input>
			   
	methods of http that forms use : Get method		
									 Post method
									 
	Creating a form:
					<form method = get/post action = "dest page url"> 
							<input type = "text" name = "userName" />
					</form>
					
	using the get method, the eneterd data is visible in the url
	to hide that , use post method
	
	in login forms,password will be visible in url . so use post method
	with radio buttons, use get method
	
	if radio buttons belong to the same group (example - gender- male or female), use the same value for name attribute
	using diff values, makes both the buttons selectable

		value of checkboxes is either on (when selected) or off (when not selected)
		
